SIMPLE: intuitive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intuitive
<hw>In*tu"i*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intuitif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Seeing clearly; <as>as, an <ex>intuitive</ex> view;
<ex>intuitive</ex> vision.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Knowing, or perceiving, by intuition; capable of
knowing without deduction or reasoning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whence the soul⟦br⟧
Reason receives, and reason is her being,⟦br⟧
Discursive, or <qex>intuitive</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Received, reached, obtained, or perceived, by
intuition; <as>as, <ex>intuitive</ex> judgment or knowledge</as>; --
opposed to <contr>deductive</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intuitively</ent>⟦br⟧
